(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, while 
exerc ising the powers under clause ( v) of sub -section (2), the Authority shall have the 
same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 
1908) while trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely — 

(a) the discovery and production of books of account and other documents, at such 
place and at such time as may be specified;  
(b) summoning and enforcing the attendance of persons and examining them on oath;  
(c) inspection of any book, document, register or record o f any data fiduciary ;  
(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;  
(e) any other matter which may be prescribed.  

